               <msContents>
                  <summary>The recto contains the beginning of a letter preserving opening greetings ('[may He amelior]ate His blessing on you') and a remark about the sender's family's well-being ('[and those who are with me] are in good health, praise be [to God]'). The sender hopes for something. The verso preserves part of the address with the name of the addressee as Abu al-Fadl.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Recto (perpendicular to fibres) contains 6 lines and has a small blank margin at the top.</note>
                     <note type="general">Verso (parallel to fibres) has 1 line and also a blank margin at the top.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar-Arab">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
